div.p:
               SALOMON ſayth, that Hope deferred breaks the heart; but the
deſire obtayned, is a Tree of Life: If Hope onely deferred breake the Heart;
then Hope fruſtrated muſt needs breake it a great deale more.

I admoniſh him that ſhal trie with the Tiffany upon the
dew, to let his hands be waſhed before with ſope & hot water;
& wiped with a pure white cloth, til they wil not foule the cloth at al;
elſe if they ſpend their mony in digging, & find

nothing, they may thank their foule fingers for
that misfortune.
